Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.33,0:00:16.67,Title,,0,0,0,,{\pos(640,110)\fad(1300,1500)\blur4}The Count of Monte Cristo
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.70,0:00:06.99,OP-English,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,300)}So tonight I'll sing a song to all my friends
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.12,0:00:11.83,OP-English,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,300)}Also to those we won't be seeing again
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.21,0:00:16.34,OP-English,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,300)}To those I knew and those I still adore
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.34,0:00:19.05,OP-English,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,300)}And I want to see once more
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.05,0:00:25.89,OP-English,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,300)}I just pray that you will love me and trust me
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.14,0:00:30.73,OP-English,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,300)}Laugh with me and cry with me
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.10,0:00:35.77,OP-English,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,300)}Spend those silent times with me
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.90,0:00:39.90,OP-English,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,300)}Love me ever more
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.40,0:00:44.78,OP-English,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,300)}Love me ever more
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.28,0:00:51.37,OP-English,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,300)}You and I were lovers
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.37,0:00:55.33,OP-English,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,300)}Our dreams were not soured by life
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.54,0:01:01.09,OP-English,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,300)}And then my friends' betrayal
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.09,0:01:08.35,OP-English,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,500)}Meant you never would be my wife
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.27,0:01:13.27,OP-English,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,300)}Harsh words were said
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.27,0:01:15.98,OP-English,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,300)}And lies were told instead
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.44,0:01:21.65,OP-English,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,500)}I didn't ever mean to make you cry
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.67,0:01:33.61,gankutsuou,,0,0,0,,Ladies and gentlemen, good evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.61,0:01:37.61,gankutsuou,,0,0,0,,On that stormy day that announced the end of spring,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.71,0:01:41.84,gankutsuou,,0,0,0,,...my friend and I arrived in Paris, where the boy awaited us.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.87,0:01:47.81,gankutsuou,,0,0,0,,I tremble in silence at these emotions which leak out...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.25,0:01:50.84,gankutsuou,,0,0,0,,...as the hour of reunion draws near.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.79,0:01:57.05,count main,,0,0,0,,This must be your guest.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.91,0:02:19.07,count main,,0,0,0,,Count, if you don't mind, I'd like you to join us for dinner after you've met my parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.19,0:02:28.45,count main,,0,0,0,,Count?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.16,0:02:33.72,count main,,0,0,0,,If it is not too much trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.90,0:02:39.23,count main,,0,0,0,,Please do. After all, we owe you our son's life.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.00,0:02:42.73,count main,,0,0,0,,Welcome to our home,\Nmy good Count of Monte Cristo.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.02,0:02:54.02,count fo,,0,0,0,,{\pos(640,525)}Act 4:\NA Mother's Secrets
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.69,0:03:01.49,count main,,0,0,0,,To our new friend, the\NCount of Monte Cristo.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.50,0:03:08.09,count main,,0,0,0,,Oh, is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.20,0:03:11.89,count main,,0,0,0,,I'm embarrassed that you\Nknow of the Janina campaign.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.70,0:03:15.73,count main,,0,0,0,,The people praise me as a hero,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.94,0:03:18.57,count main,,0,0,0,,...but to a soldier, such things mean little.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.91,0:03:21.71,count main,,0,0,0,,After all, nothing good ever results from destruction.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.81,0:03:26.44,count main,,0,0,0,,No, these idyllic times in which we live were built on the back of sacrifice.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.58,0:03:28.31,count main,,0,0,0,,Such is my opinion, at any rate.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.42,0:03:30.89,count main,,0,0,0,,I expect that the far corners of the galaxy are echoing...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.99,0:03:33.11,count main,,0,0,0,,...with the name of\NGeneral Morcerf by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.62,0:03:35.59,count main,,0,0,0,,You honor me by saying so.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.44,0:03:54.40,count main,,0,0,0,,Oh, dear, the food wasn't to your liking?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.61,0:03:58.64,count main,,0,0,0,,Not at all. Please, think nothing of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.15,0:04:03.14,count main,,0,0,0,,I am in the habit of eating very little.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.52,0:04:07.08,count main,,0,0,0,,I can't say that I don't understand how you feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.56,0:04:12.79,count main,,0,0,0,,Having advanced in years, I find myself\Nweary of extravagant meals such as this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.30,0:04:16.66,count main,,0,0,0,,In my case, I find lately that I seldom sleep, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.07,0:04:20.36,count main,,0,0,0,,I'm amazed that you've managed to stay healthy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.70,0:04:23.60,count main,,0,0,0,,It is because of these.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.64,0:04:26.27,count main,,0,0,0,,Are they some sort of space rations?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.38,0:04:29.44,count main,,0,0,0,,In the course of wandering the sea of stars for so long,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.68,0:04:33.05,count main,,0,0,0,,...my body and soul have changed beyond recognition.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.42,0:04:37.37,count main,,0,0,0,,Even so, I hope that you\Nwould at least eat something...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.25,0:04:41.15,count main,,0,0,0,,The thought of neither sleeping nor eating is too sad to bear.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.49,0:04:42.72,count main,,0,0,0,,Too sad to bear?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.92,0:04:44.36,count main,,0,0,0,,Very well, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.93,0:04:49.40,count main,,0,0,0,,In that case, perhaps\NI shall sample this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.47,0:04:51.90,count main,,0,0,0,,Please do.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.71,0:05:07.68,count main,,0,0,0,,This taste brings back memories...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.85,0:05:09.28,count main,,0,0,0,,Brings back memories?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.38,0:05:13.48,count main,,0,0,0,,I once experienced delightful cooking such as this in the south of France.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.16,0:05:18.32,count main,,0,0,0,,This is the dish that you've made for as long as I can remember, right, Mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.23,0:05:20.16,count main,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.26,0:05:23.66,count main,,0,0,0,,By any chance, you wouldn't happen to be from Marseilles, would you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.07,0:05:24.83,count main,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.93,0:05:28.60,count main,,0,0,0,,My wife has nothing to do\Nwith such a barbaric province.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.74,0:05:30.83,count main,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right,\NMercedes?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.91,0:05:32.60,count main,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.18,0:05:34.57,count main,,0,0,0,,Oh, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.68,0:05:36.17,count main,,0,0,0,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.05,0:05:39.45,count main,,0,0,0,,One of my friends is from there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.78,0:05:43.48,count main,,0,0,0,,His name is Maximilien Morrel.\NHe's a really nice person.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.69,0:05:44.91,count main,,0,0,0,,Morrel...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.22,0:05:50.39,count main,,0,0,0,,Forgive me if I misspoke.\NPlease, do not take offense.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.19,0:05:53.66,count main,,0,0,0,,That's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.96,0:05:58.63,count main,,0,0,0,,Our family traces its roots back to a powerful Catalan family.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.53,0:06:02.26,count main,,0,0,0,,This soup has been a specialty of my\Nwife's ever since she was a young girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.37,0:06:06.20,count main,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see. So, you and the Countess were childhood friends, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.31,0:06:07.47,count main,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.58,0:06:11.81,count main,,0,0,0,,Which explains why you seem so close.\NI am jealous beyond words.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.55,0:06:17.14,count main,,0,0,0,,I had no idea that a man like you could be jealous of anyone, Count.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.25,0:06:18.69,count main,,0,0,0,,Yes, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.89,0:06:21.48,count main,,0,0,0,,If that person is a man of your father's caliber.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.32,0:06:25.99,count main,,0,0,0,,Get the Count something to drink.\NHis glass is empty.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.40,0:06:36.96,count main,,0,0,0,,Please stay for as long as time permits.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.44,0:06:41.34,count main,,0,0,0,,Sitting around the table like this, it almost feels as if you are a member of the family.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.65,0:06:54.42,count main,,0,0,0,,What a maddening scent this is...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.79,0:06:55.95,count main,,0,0,0,,Count?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.56,0:06:58.42,count main,,0,0,0,,It is from the muscat grapes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.19,0:07:01.46,count main,,0,0,0,,Are you fatigued?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.56,0:07:08.26,count main,,0,0,0,,No, please forgive me for forcing you to eat earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.60,0:07:12.44,count main,,0,0,0,,Not at all. I had always hoped to\Nexperience that delicious flavor again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.11,0:07:15.44,count main,,0,0,0,,It was a sublime experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.88,0:07:17.61,count main,,0,0,0,,It was a simple rustic dish.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.71,0:07:20.65,count main,,0,0,0,,But it makes me happy to hear you say so.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.25,0:07:27.78,count main,,0,0,0,,Have you heard of this?\NThere is a saying that goes,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.89,0:07:32.85,count main,,0,0,0,,"Those who share bread and salt under the same roof become eternal friends."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.73,0:07:36.20,count main,,0,0,0,,That is a tradition handed down\Nin Eastern Space, is it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.30,0:07:37.23,count main,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.33,0:07:42.20,count main,,0,0,0,,Which means that we are now friends.\NFor all eternity.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.84,0:07:47.60,count main,,0,0,0,,However, this is not Eastern Space.\NIt is Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.18,0:07:53.81,count main,,0,0,0,,In Paris, everlasting friendship is impossible without the act of sharing bread and salt.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.65,0:07:58.95,count main,,0,0,0,,Your soup truly was delicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.15,0:08:02.35,count main,,0,0,0,,Warm, and yet evocative of past memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.56,0:08:05.19,count main,,0,0,0,,It is something which gives comfort.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.29,0:08:08.52,count main,,0,0,0,,Like a breeze blowing across the Mediterranean Sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.63,0:08:12.83,count main,,0,0,0,,Count, are you very familiar with Marseilles?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.50,0:08:15.80,count main,,0,0,0,,I could say that\NI am aware of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.41,0:08:21.21,count main,,0,0,0,,But perhaps I never truly knew it at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.84,0:08:25.97,count main,,0,0,0,,Infidelity. Adultery.\NDalliances in the dead of night.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.58,0:08:30.31,count main,,0,0,0,,You aristocrats are as energetic as the rumors say.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.52,0:08:32.11,count main,,0,0,0,,Spare me your crude comments!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.45,0:08:34.15,count main,,0,0,0,,The Count is a friend of mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.26,0:08:35.98,count main,,0,0,0,,Honestly, you're such a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.63,0:08:40.32,count main,,0,0,0,,If people could become friends simply by sharing bread and salt,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.43,0:08:41.62,count main,,0,0,0,,...life would be simpler.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.73,0:08:42.99,count main,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.37,0:08:45.96,count main,,0,0,0,,You'll understand sooner or later, little boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.58,0:08:58.64,count main,,0,0,0,,I am most grateful to you for allowing me to experience a day such as today.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.98,0:09:04.08,count main,,0,0,0,,Not at all. I'm proud that I had the\Nopportunity to introduce you to my parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.02,0:09:06.61,count main,,0,0,0,,To introduce a man I admire.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.16,0:09:09.12,count main,,0,0,0,,What say you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.22,0:09:13.06,count main,,0,0,0,,I would like to invite you to my residence on the Champs-Elysees in the near future.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.26,0:09:15.66,count main,,0,0,0,,I'd love to come!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.40,0:09:19.39,count main,,0,0,0,,The Count of Monte Cristo was a\Nmysterious man, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.83,0:09:24.40,count main,,0,0,0,,Yes. There was a sternness somewhere in him that keeps people at arm's length.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.51,0:09:28.50,count main,,0,0,0,,That just means that compared to the Count, the people of Paris are dull.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.61,0:09:29.41,count main,,0,0,0,,My...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.01,0:09:33.64,count main,,0,0,0,,You might not know this, Mother, but there's more to the world than Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.42,0:09:38.08,count main,,0,0,0,,Out beyond the walls, there's a world that's endlessly captivating.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.95,0:09:41.95,count main,,0,0,0,,I think you've changed since your journey to Luna.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.09,0:09:45.15,count main,,0,0,0,,My journey is just beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.59,0:09:48.49,count main,,0,0,0,,Don't go to worlds too far removed from our own.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.83,0:09:52.56,count main,,0,0,0,,You should exercise moderation in your association with the Count.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.67,0:09:56.16,count main,,0,0,0,,Oh, please, Mother...\NYou sound just like Franz.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.57,0:09:58.77,count main,,0,0,0,,Well, even though he seems more than a little shady,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.87,0:10:01.74,count main,,0,0,0,,...having the Morcerf family establish ties with a man like him might not be a bad thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.31,0:10:05.64,count main,,0,0,0,,Not when this family is about to\Nthrow its hat into the political arena.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.65,0:10:11.95,count main,,0,0,0,,Good grief, why do aristocrats\Neat like this all the time?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.05,0:10:14.28,count main,,0,0,0,,Dinner parties, high tea, balls...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.42,0:10:17.05,count main,,0,0,0,,It's probably because they\Ndon't have anything else to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.56,0:10:20.65,count main,,0,0,0,,In other words, if you took away the gluttony, lust, and avarice,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.76,0:10:22.06,count main,,0,0,0,,...there wouldn't be anything left.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.16,0:10:24.50,count main,,0,0,0,,You need to watch your mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.07,0:10:29.03,count main,,0,0,0,,Didn't you think that their guest today was rather elegant and handsome?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.14,0:10:31.44,count main,,0,0,0,,I'm not so sure.\NHe wasn't very refined.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.54,0:10:36.24,count main,,0,0,0,,Maybe, but he had a pretty good vibe going with the mistress under the grapevine trellis.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.38,0:10:41.82,count main,,0,0,0,,What, really? I'd always thought that the master was the only man in the world for the mistress.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.88,0:10:45.48,count main,,0,0,0,,I think that any society lady would fall for that Count if he worked his mojo on her.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.82,0:10:47.45,count main,,0,0,0,,Give it a rest, already!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.96,0:10:52.89,count main,,0,0,0,,That was definitely the face of a woman in love.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.26,0:10:55.13,count main,,0,0,0,,If you don't stop that,\NI'm going to report you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.26,0:10:56.63,count main,,0,0,0,,Oo, I'm so scared...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.47,0:11:01.83,count main,,0,0,0,,That's preposterous. Mother is the last person in the world who would be capable of...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.84,0:11:11.11,count main,,0,0,0,,Mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.42,0:11:20.39,count main,,0,0,0,,Who's in that picture she's looking at?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.56,0:11:30.09,count main,,0,0,0,,Do you find me a horrible man?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.80,0:11:33.86,count main,,0,0,0,,No. I will stay at your side for as long as I live.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.20,0:11:37.43,count main,,0,0,0,,Even if that means walking down the path to ruin.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.94,0:11:41.10,count main,,0,0,0,,It is not we who will be ruined.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.13,0:12:04.90,count main,,0,0,0,,I have come home,\NFather.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.62,0:12:22.01,count main,,0,0,0,,What, you're still here?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.59,0:12:25.78,count main,,0,0,0,,Hey, don't touch those!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.89,0:12:28.36,count main,,0,0,0,,I hate to break it to you, but I've gotten into your father's good graces,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.46,0:12:30.65,count main,,0,0,0,,...so I'll be staying here for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.76,0:12:32.12,count main,,0,0,0,,His "good graces"?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.46,0:12:35.86,count main,,0,0,0,,It means that your father is a man like any other.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.57,0:12:40.33,count main,,0,0,0,,Give those bad jokes a rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.44,0:12:42.43,count main,,0,0,0,,Well, setting aside your father for the moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.54,0:12:45.87,count main,,0,0,0,,...the one that I'd be worried about is your mother, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.31,0:12:47.64,count main,,0,0,0,,What's that supposed to mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.91,0:12:51.85,count main,,0,0,0,,I mean, she was staring so wistfully at that picture of a young man...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.81,0:12:53.80,count main,,0,0,0,,You saw that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.92,0:12:56.11,count main,,0,0,0,,It was definitely a picture of a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.45,0:12:58.42,count main,,0,0,0,,A man who wasn't your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.02,0:13:02.28,count main,,0,0,0,,Oh, I can understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.42,0:13:04.98,count main,,0,0,0,,If my mother was staring at a picture of some strange man,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.13,0:13:06.53,count main,,0,0,0,,...l'd be depressed, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.66,0:13:08.03,count main,,0,0,0,,That's about enough!\NGet out!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.03,0:13:09.39,count main,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.08,0:13:25.05,count main,,0,0,0,,Eugenie? I didn't know you were here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.21,0:13:27.18,count main,,0,0,0,,Ever the late riser,\NI see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.32,0:13:29.41,count main,,0,0,0,,Why are you dressed like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.22,0:13:31.21,count main,,0,0,0,,What's wrong with it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.29,0:13:33.55,count main,,0,0,0,,Skirts just don't work on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.76,0:13:36.05,count main,,0,0,0,,I didn't come here to see you, Albert!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.46,0:13:38.55,count main,,0,0,0,,Then don't have me dragged out of bed!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.83,0:13:42.85,count main,,0,0,0,,I'm the one who had you woken up, Albert.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.27,0:13:49.86,count main,,0,0,0,,Is something the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.97,0:13:50.87,count main,,0,0,0,,No, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.87,0:13:53.40,count main,,0,0,0,,Eugenie is your fiancee, isn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.51,0:13:56.24,count main,,0,0,0,,I think it's only natural that you should greet her when she's over.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.78,0:14:00.18,count main,,0,0,0,,Sure, I suppose.\NUm, are you going somewhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.32,0:14:02.55,count main,,0,0,0,,Oh, we're just going out to do a little shopping together.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.88,0:14:04.55,count main,,0,0,0,,Let's go, Madame!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.75,0:14:05.72,count main,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.59,0:14:12.92,count main,,0,0,0,,That reminds me. What's this I hear about the\NCount of Monte Cristo inviting you over?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.46,0:14:14.59,count main,,0,0,0,,How did you know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.70,0:14:16.16,count main,,0,0,0,,I heard about it from Franz.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.53,0:14:19.69,count main,,0,0,0,,He said that he and Maximilien were also invited.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.97,0:14:21.46,count main,,0,0,0,,They were invited, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.15,0:14:38.68,count main,,0,0,0,,What's he...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.62,0:14:41.18,count main,,0,0,0,,Peppo!\NWhat are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.69,0:14:43.05,count main,,0,0,0,,Oh, hi, Albert!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.29,0:14:46.23,count main,,0,0,0,,Don't you "Oh, hi!" me!\NDon't play around with Mother's jewelry!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.29,0:14:48.02,count main,,0,0,0,,But they're so pretty!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.13,0:14:51.50,count main,,0,0,0,,If my father sees you like that,\Nthere'll be hell to pay!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.87,0:14:55.70,count main,,0,0,0,,Fine, fine.\NI'll put them back, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.18,0:15:05.61,count main,,0,0,0,,You're dying to know\Nwhat's in there, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.15,0:15:09.95,count main,,0,0,0,,It's like your mother's secret\Ntreasure is hidden inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.82,0:15:13.72,count main,,0,0,0,,Impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.72,0:15:18.02,count main,,0,0,0,,Oh, there's no such thing as a human being who doesn't have secrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.33,0:15:21.73,count main,,0,0,0,,Just like you and I share a certain secret night.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.00,0:15:24.40,count main,,0,0,0,,That only happened because\NI was tricked by you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.80,0:15:28.39,count main,,0,0,0,,If you ever want that lock opened, come tell me anytime.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.77,0:15:31.00,count main,,0,0,0,,I specialize in getting into people's drawers.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.67,0:15:33.70,count main,,0,0,0,,Stop being crude, and get back to work!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.14,0:15:35.30,count main,,0,0,0,,Oh. Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.93,0:15:52.79,count main,,0,0,0,,It can't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.26,0:15:56.32,count main,,0,0,0,,Why would Mother have a picture of the Count?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.74,0:16:07.04,count main,,0,0,0,,This is ridiculous.\NWhat am I so worried about?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.79,0:16:27.28,count main,,0,0,0,,His Excellency General Morcerf!\NTen-hut!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.68,0:16:42.07,count main,,0,0,0,,All high and mighty...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.08,0:16:52.58,count main,,0,0,0,,How do I look?\NNot too strange, I hope?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.69,0:16:54.71,count main,,0,0,0,,It looks wonderful on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.32,0:16:57.05,count main,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.16,0:17:00.25,count main,,0,0,0,,Thank goodness.\NYou're more upbeat than I expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.96,0:17:01.76,count main,,0,0,0,,Gee, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.86,0:17:07.50,count main,,0,0,0,,For a visit to the Count's place, that outfit isn't quite flamboyant enough, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.80,0:17:12.00,count main,,0,0,0,,Not flamboyant enough?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.98,0:17:20.47,count main,,0,0,0,,Albert? What in the world are you wearing?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.58,0:17:21.64,count main,,0,0,0,,What's wrong with it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.75,0:17:23.08,count main,,0,0,0,,Where do I even begin?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.08,0:17:25.48,count main,,0,0,0,,I'll never understand the ways of you aristocrats.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.59,0:17:27.61,count main,,0,0,0,,Why are you dressed like a pirate?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.86,0:17:31.05,count main,,0,0,0,,Uh, what are you even doing here, Beauchamp?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.23,0:17:35.86,count main,,0,0,0,,You don't expect me to miss my chance to get photos of the Count's mansion, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.73,0:17:41.17,count main,,0,0,0,,Oh, brother. And here I had hoped to go there by myself, if at all possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.90,0:17:47.84,count main,,0,0,0,,That day when I first met you, you made me realize that there is always hope,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.94,0:17:51.57,count main,,0,0,0,,...regardless of the circumstances you might find yourself in.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.85,0:17:55.87,count main,,0,0,0,,I will never forget that lesson.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.65,0:17:59.38,count main,,0,0,0,,Hope...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.39,0:18:05.72,count main,,0,0,0,,When I was flung out of the Chateau d'lf into the black void of space,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.66,0:18:11.96,count main,,0,0,0,,...hope was the one thing that I had in my possession.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.78,0:18:25.80,count main,,0,0,0,,You're sure this is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.91,0:18:29.37,count main,,0,0,0,,Yep. number thirty, Champs-Elysees.\NNo doubt about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.72,0:18:32.35,count main,,0,0,0,,It's a lot more austere than I expected it to be, considering the Count.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.45,0:18:37.76,count main,,0,0,0,,I was expecting the sort of place that would drive a commoner into a rage if he saw it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.70,0:18:49.64,count main,,0,0,0,,Welcome, messieurs.\NWe have been expecting you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.51,0:18:54.60,count main,,0,0,0,,Early Rococo, huh?\NAnd not Revival, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.61,0:18:58.91,count main,,0,0,0,,Isn't this amazing?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.01,0:19:02.11,count main,,0,0,0,,Well, it's a bit too far removed from my world...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.85,0:19:08.81,count main,,0,0,0,,Please pardon the delay.\NAllow me to show you to the Count.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.02,0:19:10.76,count main,,0,0,0,,What the...?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.76,0:19:12.12,count main,,0,0,0,,We're going down!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.29,0:19:15.32,count main,,0,0,0,,Baptistin, where are we going?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.91,0:19:33.21,count main,,0,0,0,,We've stopped!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.22,0:19:38.91,count main,,0,0,0,,Welcome, messieurs.\NThe Count awaits.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.69,0:19:40.92,count main,,0,0,0,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.14,0:20:02.87,count main,,0,0,0,,Even the floor and columns are gold...\NThe man has expensive tastes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.21,0:20:06.44,count main,,0,0,0,,Where could he have gotten this much gold?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.25,0:20:09.77,count main,,0,0,0,,That's why I think there's something fishy about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.92,0:20:12.89,count main,,0,0,0,,At this rate, I bet his bed and\Npillows are gonna be solid gold, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.22,0:20:15.09,count main,,0,0,0,,I'd never be able to fall asleep with all this glare.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.19,0:20:16.38,count main,,0,0,0,,Hey! Look at that!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.93,0:20:20.26,count main,,0,0,0,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.83,0:20:21.80,count main,,0,0,0,,The sea?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.80,0:20:23.79,count main,,0,0,0,,No, wait.\NLook at that sky!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.63,0:20:27.62,count main,,0,0,0,,It's artificial?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.74,0:20:29.26,count main,,0,0,0,,I can't believe it...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.87,0:20:32.34,count main,,0,0,0,,This alone would make one hell of a story.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.48,0:20:41.31,count main,,0,0,0,,This is so beautiful...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.98,0:20:44.61,count main,,0,0,0,,Wait, I know this view!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.29,0:20:54.35,count main,,0,0,0,,That look suits you quite well, Sir Pirate.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.76,0:20:55.69,count main,,0,0,0,,Count!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.40,0:21:00.42,count main,,0,0,0,,Wha...?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.75,0:21:14.37,count main,,0,0,0,,If you don't mind, I would like\Nyou to have this, Sir Pirate.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.25,0:21:23.55,count main,,0,0,0,,I was given this blade by a certain ship's navigator.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.06,0:21:31.56,count main,,0,0,0,,Perhaps it will serve to protect you, as well as to carve a path for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.66,0:23:12.26,count main,,0,0,0,,When we meet someone,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.07,0:23:15.83,count main,,0,0,0,,...the selfless, considerate part of us clashes with the selfish love of our emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.24,0:23:18.51,count main,,0,0,0,,Next time on Gankutsuou,\NThe Count of Monte Cristo, act 5,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.45,0:23:20.58,count fo,,0,0,0,,{\pos(640,525)}Act 5:\NDo You Love Your Fiancee?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.71,0:23:20.87,count main,,0,0,0,,..."Do You Love Your Fiancee?"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.21,0:23:23.18,count main,,0,0,0,,Bide your time, and hold out hope!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.64,0:21:57.69,ED-English,,0,0,0,,{\blur7\fad(300,300)}I'm not the man I used to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.07,0:22:08.41,ED-English,,0,0,0,,{\blur7\fad(300,300)}And what you see is not what it seems.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.49,0:22:15.00,ED-English,,0,0,0,,{\blur7\fad(300,300)}I traveled through space to be with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.00,0:22:23.63,ED-English,,0,0,0,,{\blur7\fad(300,300)}What you don't know, you shouldn't fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.72,0:22:31.85,ED-English,,0,0,0,,{\blur7\fad(300,300)}You won't see me coming,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.23,0:22:40.36,ED-English,,0,0,0,,{\blur7\fad(300,300)}you won't see me coming
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.77,0:22:43.36,ED-English,,0,0,0,,{\blur7\fad(300,300)}till I strike!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.12,0:22:57.25,ED-English,,0,0,0,,{\blur7\fad(300,300)}You won't see me coming,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.67,0:23:05.76,ED-English,,0,0,0,,{\blur7\fad(300,300)}you won't see me coming
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.26,0:23:08.89,ED-English,,0,0,0,,{\blur7\fad(300,300)}till I strike!
